    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 5 Engine Service Manual - Rear Cover and Flywheel - Installation - Rear
        Main Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="9">
        <title>Rear Main Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve</title>
        <svcsubproc id="s26513.3.3">
            <title>CityStar&#8482;Applications</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not separate wear sleeve from the new oil seal, damage to seal
                        and engine will result.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>When replacing the rear main oil seal it should be noted that production engines not
                        previously serviced, will not have a wear sleeve. Wear sleeves are only available as a service
                        item included with a rear main oil seal service kit.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean primary crankshaft flange a with suitable solvent. Dry with filtered compressed
                    air.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001420" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06027.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Sealant application to crankshaft primary flange (CityStar&#8482;)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a 360&#176; bead of
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_309.xml" xrefid="E30014C">Loctite&#174; Hydraulic Sealant</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="E30014C"/>
                    onto the rear edge of the crankshaft primary flange prior to wear sleeve and rear main oil seal
                    installation.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001421" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06028.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Rear Seal / Wear Sleeve Installer (CityStar&#8482;)</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Bolt Rear Seal / Wear Sleeve installer onto end of crankshaft. Make sure crankshaft
                    dowel fits in installation tool dowel recess hole.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001423" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd07/D0727.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Rear main oil seal and wear sleeve</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Dust seal lip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear main oil seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft side (forward)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Wear sleeve (internal bevel)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="e3001425" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06031.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Rear main seal / wear sleeve installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear main oil seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear Seal / Wear Sleeve Installer</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Thrust bearing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Drive nut</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position rear main oil seal and wear sleeve combination on the Rear Seal / Wear Sleeve
                    Installer. Make sure the beveled edge of the wear sleeve is oriented toward the crankshaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place thrust bearing and drive nut onto threaded shaft. Tighten nut until rear main oil
                    seal bottoms out onto rear oil seal carrier.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the Rear Seal/Wear Sleeve Installer tool.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="e3001426" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Flywheel adapter (CityStar&#8482;)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Dowel pin</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pin recess</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Flywheel adapter</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not scratch crankshaft primary flange sealing surface.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place flywheel adaptor onto crankshaft primary flange. Be sure to line up dowel pin. If
                    necessary, carefully tap with hammer to start and seat.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Stripped Chassis Applications</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not separate wear sleeve from oil seal, damage to the seal and
                        engine will result.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>When replacing the rear main oil seal, note that production engines will not have a wear
                        sleeve. Wear sleeves are only available as a service item included with the replacement rear
                        main oil seal.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2651333" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd07/D0748.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Sealant application to crankshaft secondary flange</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place a 360&#176; bead of Loctite&#174; Hydraulic Sealant onto the rear edge of the
                    crankshaft secondary flange prior to wear sleeve and rear main oil seal installation. See
                    <hotlnk document="eges390_309.xml" xrefid="E30014C">Special Service Tools
                        <xref refid="E30014C"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651331" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figJ06/J06081.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Rear Seal / Wear Sleeve Installer</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Bolt Rear Seal / Wear Sleeve Installer
                    <xref refid="te30014C"/>
                    onto the end of secondary crankshaft flange. Make sure crankshaft alignment dowel fits in dowel
                    recess hole.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651332" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd07/D0727.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Rear main oil seal and wear sleeve orientation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Dust seal lip</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear main oil seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankshaft side (forward)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Wear sleeve (internal bevel)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Orient seal as shown in
                    <xref refid="f2651332"/>
                    and slide on Rear Seal / Wear Sleeve Installer. Make sure the beveled edge of the wear sleeve is
                    oriented toward the crankshaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position rear main oil seal and wear sleeve combination on the Rear Seal / Wear Sleeve
                    Installer.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2651335" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd07/D0724.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Rear main oil seal and wear sleeve combination</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear Seal / Wear Sleeve Installer</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Rear main oil seal</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Drive nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Thrust bearing</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place thrust bearing and drive nut onto threaded shaft. Tighten nut until rear main oil
                    seal bottoms out in rear oil seal carrier.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
